commitResults.messageTitle: Save tasks when list changes and load data on start.
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, tasks added or updated are not saved when the program is terminated.

Tasks must be saved as users may require the list of tasks the next time they use the program.

Let's save accumulated tasks in a duke.txt file automatically whenever the task list changes and load the task list from the file when the chatbot starts up.

Having a specific file to store the task list allows changes to be saved and loaded easily.

Deadlines are treated as simply strings.

We need to have some form of checking the string input to ensure that a proper date and time is inputted.

Let's verify that the date and time inputted by the user is valid and store it in the Deadline object as a LocalDateTime object.

By doing so, we can be sure that the user has inputted a valid deadline and code is more organised.

commitResults.messageTitle: Manually committing to merge with Level-8 branch
Structure the code using more OOP.
commitResults.messageBody:
Most of the code is cluttered in the Duke.java file.

This makes the card hard to read, and makes it harder to change when the code is not segmented.

Let's edit the code and use more OOP!

Incorporating more OOP makes the code easier to read and more scalable as related fields and methods are grouped together.

commitResults.messageTitle: Encapsulate files in a duke package.
commitResults.messageBody:
All files are currently in the src/main/java directory.

The files must be encapsulated as it is easier to determine which files are related to which.

Let's place all files in a package and include them in that package.

By putting all files under a package, it encapsulates the Duke chatbot and its functionalities.
